# Enterprise Network Requirements

## Overview

This document outlines the requirements for building a complete
enterprise IT infrastructure to support a fictional business. Teams will
design, implement, and operate a fully functional network environment
that demonstrates real-world system administration capabilities.

The goal is to create an infrastructure that not only works technically
but also supports actual business operations---selling goods and
services, communicating with customers, managing data, and maintaining
security.

###  

### Starting Network Topology

Teams begin with a pre-configured three-zone network architecture:

\[Internet\]

\|

\[External Switch\]

\|

\[Router-WAN\]\-\-\--\[Security Desktop\]

172.31.0.1 172.31.0.100

\|

\[WAN Switch\]

\|

\[Firewall\]

192.168.2.2

/ \\

\[Screened Subnet \[Firewall Switch\]

Switch\] \|

\| \[Router-LAN\]

\| 192.168.1.1

\| \|

\| \[Internal Switch\]

\| \|

+\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\--+\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\--+
+\-\-\-\-\--+\-\-\-\-\--+\-\-\-\-\--+\-\-\-\-\--+

\| \| \| \| \| \| \|

\[WebServer\] \[Database\] \[Client1\]\[Client2\]\[AD/DNS\]\[Tracker\]

10.0.1.100 10.0.1.200 .100 .101 .5 .10

**Network Zones:**

-   **WAN Zone (172.31.0.X)**: External-facing network with security
    > monitoring

-   **Screened Subnet (10.0.1.X)**: Semi-trusted zone for public-facing
    > services (web server, database)

-   **Internal LAN (192.168.1.X)**: Trusted internal network for
    > workstations and core services

This architecture implements defense-in-depth principles by segmenting
the network into zones with different trust levels, controlled by the
central firewall.

## 1. Business Concept

### Purpose

Every technical decision should serve a business purpose. Before
building infrastructure, teams must define what their organization does
and who it serves. This grounds technical work in real-world context and
helps prioritize which systems matter most.

### Requirements

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Requirement**                     **Description**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  Define at least three goods         Identify three physical or digital
                                      products your business sells

  Define at least three services      Identify three services your
                                      business offers to customers
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Assessment Criteria

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Task**                **Success Measure**     **Notes**
  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------
  Identified at least     Goods are visible and   Should be realistic for
  three goods             purchasable on the      the business type
                          company website         

  Identified at least     Services are visible    Services should
  three services          and purchasable on the  complement the goods
                          company website         offered
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

