## 2. Project Management

### Purpose

Enterprise IT projects fail more often from poor planning than from
technical problems. Project management skills---tracking tasks,
visualizing timelines, documenting architecture---are essential for
coordinating team efforts and communicating progress to stakeholders.

### Requirements

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Requirement**                     **Description**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  Gantt Chart                         Create and maintain a project
                                      timeline showing all major
                                      milestones and dependencies

  Network Diagram                     Produce an accurate Visio (or
                                      equivalent) diagram of your network
                                      topology

  Security Compliance                 Complete a CSET (Cyber Security
                                      Evaluation Tool) assessment of your
                                      infrastructure

  Kanban Board                        Maintain an active Kanban board
                                      tracking all tasks through to-do,
                                      doing, and done states
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Assessment Criteria

  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Task**                **Success Measure**     **Notes**
  ----------------------- ----------------------- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Gantt Chart             Completed chart posted  Should reflect actual project progress
                          and kept current        

  Network Diagram         Diagram accurately      Include IP addresses, hostnames, and connections
                          represents deployed     
                          infrastructure          

  Security Compliance     CSET Tool report        Use [[CISA\'s CSET
                          generated and reviewed  Tool]{.underline}](https://www.cisa.gov/resources-tools/services/cyber-security-evaluation-tool-cset)

  Kanban Maintenance      Board shows active task All team members should be moving tickets
                          movement                
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Note on CSET:** The Cyber Security Evaluation Tool (CSET) from CISA
provides a systematic approach for evaluating your security posture
against recognized government and industry standards. Download it from
[[CISA\'s download
page]{.underline}](https://www.cisa.gov/downloading-and-installing-cset)
and run assessments throughout your project to identify gaps.

## 3. Account Management

### Purpose

Identity and access management is the foundation of enterprise security.
Who can access what---and proving they are who they claim to
be---determines whether your other security controls matter at all.
Active Directory provides centralized authentication and authorization
for Windows environments, and can extend to Linux systems as well.

### Requirements

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Requirement**                     **Description**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  Network Authentication              Configure centralized
                                      authentication via Active Directory

  Domain Integration                  Join all machines (workstations and
                                      servers) to the domain, including
                                      Linux systems

  Administrative Accounts             Create and configure administrator
                                      accounts with elevated privileges

  Standard User Accounts              Create standard user accounts with
                                      appropriate access levels

  Guest/Consultant Accounts           Create limited-access accounts for
                                      temporary or external users
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Assessment Criteria

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Task**                **Success Measure**     **Notes**
  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------
  Network authentication  Successfully access the AD/DNS server should be
  configured              network admin console   functional

  Windows machines        All Windows             Verify in AD Users and
  domain-joined           workstations and        Computers
                          servers appear in       
                          Active Directory        

  Linux machines          Red Hat systems         Users can log in with
  domain-joined           authenticate against    domain credentials
                          Active Directory        

  Admin account           Log in as admin and     Test elevated privilege
  functional              perform administrative  operations
                          tasks                   

  User accounts           Log in as a standard    Verify appropriate
  functional              user                    access restrictions

  Guest account           Log in as guest with    Should have minimal
  functional              limited access          permissions
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

