## 7. AI Infrastructure

### Purpose

Artificial intelligence is transforming how organizations operate,
interact with customers, and secure their systems. Modern IT
professionals must understand how to deploy, integrate, and manage AI
systems. This includes creating customer-facing AI applications and
building automated workflows that can operate autonomously.

### Requirements

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Requirement**                     **Description**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  AI Chatbot                          Deploy at least one AI-powered
                                      chatbot on your customer-facing
                                      website

  GPU API Integration                 Make API calls to Cyberlab\'s GPU
                                      infrastructure for AI model
                                      inference

  Agentic Workflow                    Create at least one agentic
                                      workflow that can make decisions
                                      and take actions autonomously
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Assessment Criteria

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Task**                **Success Measure**     **Notes**
  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------
  Chatbot deployed        Chatbot accessible on   Should provide useful
                          website and responds to business-related
                          customer queries        responses

  GPU API functional      Demonstrate successful  Show request/response
                          API calls to Cyberlab   for AI inference
                          GPU resources           

  Agentic workflow        Workflow executes       Document the workflow
  operational             autonomously based on   logic and demonstrate
                          triggers or conditions  execution
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Examples of Agentic Workflows

Teams have flexibility in designing their agentic workflow. Examples
include:

-   **Customer Service Automation**: A workflow that monitors incoming
    > support tickets, categorizes them using AI, and either
    > auto-responds to common questions or escalates to appropriate
    > staff

-   **Security Monitoring Agent**: An autonomous system that monitors
    > logs, detects anomalies, and takes initial response actions (e.g.,
    > alerting, blocking suspicious IPs)

-   **Inventory Management**: A workflow that monitors stock levels,
    > predicts demand, and generates purchase recommendations or alerts

-   **Backup Verification Agent**: An automated system that verifies
    > backup integrity, tests restores on a schedule, and reports issues

-   **System Health Monitor**: An agent that checks system metrics,
    > compares against baselines, and initiates remediation scripts when
    > thresholds are exceeded

Workflows can be built using platforms like N8N, custom Python scripts
with AI integration, or other automation tools.

## 8. Workstations

### Purpose

End-user workstations are where employees actually do their work.
Configuring workstations to properly authenticate, access services, and
run business applications demonstrates the full integration of your
infrastructure. Supporting multiple operating systems (Windows and
Linux) reflects real enterprise environments.

### Requirements

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Requirement**                     **Description**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  Workstation Deployment              Configure at least one Windows and
                                      one Red Hat Linux workstation

  Domain Integration                  Workstations authenticate against
                                      the central directory

  Service Access                      Users can access all business
                                      services from workstations

  Business Applications               Workstations have appropriate
                                      software for job functions
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Assessment Criteria

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Task**                **Success Measure**     **Notes**
  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------
  Workstations deployed   1 Windows, 1 Red Hat    Both should be
                          workstation operational domain-joined

  Authentication works    Any user can            Test with different
                          authenticate and access user types
                          network resources       

  Email accessible        Users can send/receive  Test email client
                          email from workstations configuration

  Web services accessible Users can access        Browser-based access
                          website and helpdesk,   
                          submit tickets          

  Other services          Users can access        Based on role
  accessible              database and other      permissions
                          services as appropriate 

  Applications functional Business applications   Test various
                          run correctly           applications
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

## 9. Analytics

### Purpose

You cannot secure or manage what you cannot see. Monitoring and
analytics provide visibility into network traffic, system health, and
potential security incidents. Dashboards transform raw data into
actionable insights for administrators and management.

### Requirements

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Requirement**                     **Description**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  Network Monitoring                  Implement tools to capture and
                                      analyze network traffic

  Device Monitoring                   Monitor the health and status of
                                      servers and workstations

  Dashboard                           Create a consolidated view of key
                                      metrics and alerts
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Assessment Criteria

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Task**                **Success Measure**     **Notes**
  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------
  Network monitoring      Access and interpret    Should show traffic
  active                  network traffic         patterns and anomalies
                          information             

  Device monitoring       Access device health    CPU, memory, disk,
  active                  and status information  service status

  Dashboard functional    Dashboard displays      Should be useful for
                          real-time information   daily operations
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

## 10. Backup and Recovery

### Purpose

Data loss can end a business. Backup and recovery procedures ensure that
when (not if) something goes wrong, the organization can recover.
Testing these procedures is as important as implementing them---untested
backups are not backups.

### Requirements

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Requirement**                     **Description**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  Database Backup                     Configure automated backups of the
                                      database

  Recovery Testing                    Demonstrate the ability to restore
                                      the database from backup
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Assessment Criteria

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Task**                **Success Measure**     **Notes**
  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------
  Database backup         Demonstrate that        Show backup logs and
  configured              database backups are    storage location
                          running                 

  Recovery functional     Successfully restore    Perform a restore and
                          database from backup    verify data integrity
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

## 11. Network Documentation

### Purpose

When a system administrator leaves or a critical system fails at 2 AM,
documentation is what allows the organization to continue operating. A
comprehensive network document captures everything someone would need to
understand, maintain, and recover your infrastructure. This is a
professional deliverable that demonstrates your ability to document
complex systems.

### Requirements

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Requirement**                     **Description**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  System Documentation                Create and maintain a comprehensive
                                      Google Doc containing complete
                                      network documentation

  Configuration Records               Document all system configurations,
                                      IP addresses, hostnames, and
                                      network settings

  Credential Management               Record all administrative passwords
                                      and access credentials (secured
                                      appropriately)

  Software Inventory                  List all installed software,
                                      versions, and license information

  Service Documentation               Document how each service is
                                      configured and how components
                                      interconnect
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Assessment Criteria

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Task**                **Success Measure**     **Notes**
  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------
  Documentation exists    Google Doc is           Should be a living
                          accessible and          document updated
                          organized               throughout the project

  Configurations          All system              IP addresses,
  documented              configurations are      hostnames, firewall
                          recorded                rules, etc.

  Credentials recorded    All passwords and       Store securely;
                          access credentials are  essential for team
                          documented              handoffs

  Software documented     Complete inventory of   Include where software
                          installed software and  was obtained
                          versions                

  Services documented     Clear explanation of    Someone new should be
                          how services are        able to understand the
                          configured and          system
                          connected               
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

## 12. Vulnerability Assessment

### Purpose

Every system has vulnerabilities. Proactive scanning identifies
weaknesses before attackers do, allowing you to prioritize and remediate
issues. Regular vulnerability assessments are a compliance requirement
in most regulated industries and a best practice everywhere.

### Requirements

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Requirement**                     **Description**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  Vulnerability Scanning              Conduct vulnerability scans of your
                                      infrastructure

  Compliance Assessment               Use CSET to evaluate compliance
                                      with security standards

  Remediation Planning                Document identified vulnerabilities
                                      and remediation plans
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Assessment Criteria

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Task**                **Success Measure**     **Notes**
  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------
  Vulnerability scan      Scan report generated   Identify critical,
  completed               and reviewed            high, medium, and low
                                                  findings

  CSET assessment         CSET report shows       Address gaps identified
  completed               compliance status       by the tool

  Remediation documented  Plan exists for         Prioritize based on
                          addressing identified   risk
                          vulnerabilities         
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

